{"body": {"name": "DevHub Developer Contributor report by Thomas for 09/2/2024 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}09/13/2024", "summary": "Over the past two weeks, I contributed to devhub by working on migrating the queryapi indexer responsible for proposals and rfps to the subquery network. ", "category": "DevDAO Platform", "timeline": {"status": "REVIEW", "sponsor_requested_review": false, "reviewer_completed_attestation": false}, "supervisor": "theori.near", "description": "## Summary of Activities\\\\n\\\\n**Week 1: September 2 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}September 6**\\\\n\\\\nMonday September 2 - 5 hours\\\\n- Wrote two tests for [926](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/926)\\\\n- Studied the subquery network trying to deploy a PoC for proposals [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Created issue [932](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/932)\\\\n\\\\nTuesday September 3 - 4 hours\\\\n- Figuring out the workflow of SBQL network indexer. Researching how long it will take to reindex everything. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\nWednesday September 4 - 4 hours\\\\n- Attended standup\\\\n- Was trying to get the GraphQL schema created by the QueryApi\\\\\\'s SQL schema through `near-lake-js`. Ended up translating the schema myself. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Reviewed PR Megha\\\\\\'s on the MarkdownViewer [931](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/pull/931)\\\\n\\\\nThursday September 5 - 5 hours\\\\n- Had a call with the SubQL team regarding errors encountered after recent fixes and discussed the managed deployment service [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Investigated error: socket hang-up [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Figuring out why the WorkerBlockDispatcherService is stalling [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Ran into issues of Failed to fetch indexer health [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Total hours: 18 hours**\\\\n\\\\n**Week 2: September 9 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}September 13**\\\\n\\\\nMonday September 9 - 4 hours\\\\n- Continued working on [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Deployed first subquery to the IPFS and the [subquery network](https://explorer.subquery.network/subquery/Tguntenaar/devhub-test-proposal)\\\\n- Used the build-in GraphQL API over HTTP to get indexed information with [this query](https://api.subquery.network/sq/Tguntenaar/devhub-test-proposal/graphql?query={testProposals(first:5){nodes{id,authorId,receiverId}}nearActionEntities(first:5){nodes{id,sender,receiver,amount}}}) \\\\n\\\\n\\\\nTuesday September 10th - 4 hours\\\\n- Figuring out the difference between the queryAPI\\\\\\'s streamerMessage type using the `near-lake-framework-js` and the `near-api-js` Chunk and Blockheader types. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Call with Peter about identifying the new proposal id based after an add_proposal event. Ended up making a RPC call, to get_proposal_ids at a certain block_id, from the subquery handler. Took 1,5 hour [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\nWednesday September 11th - 2 hours\\\\n- Attended standup.\\\\n- Added handler handleSetBlockHeightCallback to the indexer [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\nThursday September 12th - 3 hours\\\\n- Added handleEditProposalLinkedRFP and handleEditProposal to the mappingHandlers [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Researching using the same indexer for events-committee and infrastructure committee, with the constraint that events-committee has a different starting block because of earlier tests on mainnet. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Total hours: 13 hours**\\\\n  \\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n## Cost\\\\n\\\\n- Total hours: 31\\\\n- Rate: $100/hour ~ \\\\u{20ac}90/hour is an average rate for a mid-level freelance front-end web3 developer in the Netherlands, ranging from \\\\u{20ac}35 (absolute beginner) to \\\\u{20ac}150 (senior) [for example](https://zzpservicedesk.nl/uurtarief-freelance-developer/)\\\\n- Total amount: $3100 USD\\\\n", "linked_proposals": [], "receiver_account": "thomasguntenaar.near", "requested_sponsor": "neardevdao.near", "proposal_body_version": "V0", "requested_sponsorship_usd_amount": "3100", "requested_sponsorship_paid_in_currency": "NEAR"}, "labels": [], "accepted_terms_and_conditions_version": 128344425}
